.TH "WARGS" "1" "2026\-04\-11" "Winix" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
wargs \- read items from stdin and execute a command for each one
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[I]input\f[R] \f[B]|\f[R] \f[B]wargs\f[R] [\f[I]options\f[R]]
[\f[B]\(en\f[R]] \f[I]command\f[R] [\f[I]args\f[R]\&...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Reads items from stdin and executes \f[I]command\f[R] for each one.
Line\-delimited by default.
If the command contains \f[B]{}\f[R], each item replaces the
placeholder; otherwise items are appended as trailing arguments.
.PP
Supports parallel execution (\f[B]\-P\f[R]), batching (\f[B]\-n\f[R]),
dry\-run, confirm, and structured output \(em a cross\-platform
\f[B]xargs\f[R] replacement with sane defaults.
.PP
With no \f[I]command\f[R], items are echoed to stdout (like
\f[B]echo\f[R]).
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\f[B]\-P\f[R], \f[B]\(enparallel\f[R] \f[I]N\f[R]
Maximum concurrent jobs (default: 1; 0 = unlimited).
.TP
\f[B]\-n\f[R], \f[B]\(enbatch\f[R] \f[I]N\f[R]
Items per command invocation (default: 1).
.TP
\f[B]\-0\f[R], \f[B]\(ennull\f[R]
Null\-delimited input (for use with \f[B]find \-print0\f[R]).
.TP
\f[B]\-d\f[R], \f[B]\(endelimiter\f[R] \f[I]CHAR\f[R]
Custom single\-character input delimiter.
.TP
\f[B]\(encompat\f[R]
POSIX whitespace splitting with quote handling.
.TP
\f[B]\(enfail\-fast\f[R]
Stop spawning new jobs after the first child failure.
.TP
\f[B]\-k\f[R], \f[B]\(enkeep\-order\f[R]
Print output in input order (parallel mode only).
.TP
\f[B]\(enline\-buffered\f[R]
Children inherit stdio directly (no output buffering).
.TP
\f[B]\-p\f[R], \f[B]\(enconfirm\f[R]
Prompt before each job.
.TP
\f[B]\(endry\-run\f[R]
Print commands that would be executed without running them.
.TP
\f[B]\-v\f[R], \f[B]\(enverbose\f[R]
Print each command to stderr before running it.
.TP
\f[B]\(enjson\f[R]
JSON summary to stderr on exit.
.TP
\f[B]\(enndjson\f[R]
Streaming NDJSON per job to stderr.
.TP
\f[B]\(enno\-shell\-fallback\f[R]
Disable shell fallback for shell builtins.
.TP
\f[B]\(encolor\f[R]
Force coloured output.
.TP
\f[B]\(enno\-color\f[R]
Disable coloured output.
.TP
\f[B]\(enversion\f[R]
Show version.
.TP
\f[B]\-h\f[R], \f[B]\(enhelp\f[R]
Show help.
.SH SHELL BUILTINS
Commands like \f[B]echo\f[R], \f[B]del\f[R], \f[B]type\f[R], and
\f[B]ver\f[R] are shell builtins on Windows.
By default, wargs retries failed commands via the platform shell
(\f[B]cmd /c\f[R] on Windows, \f[B]sh \-c\f[R] on Unix), so builtins
work transparently.
Use \f[B]\(enno\-shell\-fallback\f[R] to require standalone executables.
